name: Deck
desc: A "live" Deck of cards that is used for a game.

name: Deck
desc: Create a new Deck from a MasterDeck name

name: clearAll
desc: Clear all associated Hands.

name: combinations
desc:
Iterate over all distinct count-sized Hands from the remaining deck.
For this purpose, hands with the same cards in different order are
considered "distinct". For example, on a fresh 52-card deck,
for h in d.combinations(5) will iterate over all 2598960 5-card hands.

name: contains
desc: Does the Deck contain the given Card?

name: dealAll
desc:
Deal all Hands created from this deck a number of cards. Useful at
the start of a hand of play, e.g. d.dealAll(5);.

name: dealTo
desc: Deal a single card to the given Hand

name: hands
desc: Hands spawned from this deck

name: isEmpty
desc: Have all Cards been dealt?

name: isNotEmpty
desc: Are any Cards remaining?

name: iterator
desc: Implementation of iterator

name: length
desc: How many Cards remain?

name: master
desc: Associated MasterDeck from which to fill this one

name: pop
desc:
Pop a Card from the Deck. This is expected to be the primary way
cards are taken (the dealXX functions call this).

name: popN
desc: Pop a number of Cards from the Deck.

name: push
desc: Add a Card to the Deck. Not expected to be used often.

name: pushN
desc: Push a number of Cards back onto the Deck.

name: refill
desc: Refill the Deck from its associated MasterDeck.

name: remaining
desc: Handy synonym for "length"

name: removeCard
desc:
Remove a specific Card from the Deck by its identity.
(e.g. d.removeCard(Card.JackOfClubs)).

name: shuffle
desc: Randomize the Cards remaining in the Deck.

name: size
desc: How many cards in full deck?

name: sort
desc:
Sort the Deck into the same descending order by Rank and Suit as
used for Hands. Note that this will make the deck appear to be in the
reverse ascending order when printed (see toString(), below).

name: toList
desc: Copy the remaining Cards onto a new List.

name: toString
desc:
Print contents of Deck. Note that for performance, cards are popped
from the end of the list, which makes it the notional "top" of the deck.
For testing and simulation purposes, deck contents are shown backwards:
i.e., from the end of the list to the front.

name: validCard
desc:
Validate that the Card passed is legal for this deck. Convert high
and low aces if necessary.
